IP and Hostname Tools

>>> import socket
>>> socket.gethostbyname('example.com')
'93.184.216.34'


IP Address Math

>>> import ipaddress
>>> net = ipaddress.ip_network('192.168.1.0/24')
>>> list(net.hosts())[:3]
[IPv4Address('192.168.1.1'), IPv4Address('192.168.1.2'), IPv4Address('192.168.1.3')]


System Info

>>> import platform
>>> platform.uname()
uname_result(system='Linux', node='labvm', release='6.1.0', version='#1 SMP', machine='x86_64')



Exercise:
Write a one-liner to print your systemâ€™s hostname and kernel version.


python3 -c "import platform; print(platform.uname())"
python3 -c "import platform; u=platform.uname(); print(f'Hostname: {u.node}, Kernel: {u.release}')"
